We use a hash map to store the cache records. Each record contains the key, value, and a counter for the number of times the key has been accessed. When a new key is added or an existing key is accessed, we update the used_count of the key and update the value if the key exists in the cache. If the number of accesses exceeds the capacity, remove the least recently used key-value pair from the cache.

The solution has a high efficiency, as it uses a hash map to store the cache records, which has a constant time complexity (O(1)). The space complexity is also O(1) since we only use a hash map. The energy implications are low, as the solution does not require any additional energy consumption.

